Snippet tests help ensure our docs are correct. Generally, we don't use // TEST[skip:... unless absolutely necessary.  In this case,  I think the skipped test is hiding an incorrect response.
I suggested a valid response below. Here's how you can get it yourself next time:

Use a command like ./gradlew :docs:integTestRunner --tests "*create-snapshot-api*" to test the snippets in the file.
Use // TESTRESPONSE[s/.../.../] to selectively replace some properties in the response.

This is covered in more depth in the docs README: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/tree/master/docs




        Suggested change











            [source,console-result]



            ----



            {



              "accepted" : true



            }



            ----



